content.text:
Let me help you solve this block assembly task by analyzing the images:

1. Main Target Image Analysis:
- Structure composed of yellow and red blocks
- 2 layers total
- Bottom layer: 2 yellow curved/semi-circular blocks
- Top layer: 1 yellow rectangular block and 1 red triangular block
- Blocks are arranged to form a vehicle-like or bridge-like structure

2. Block Selection from Dictionary:
Required blocks (by index):
- Yellow semi-circular blocks: Block #5 and #6
- Yellow rectangular block: Block #1
- Red triangular block: Block #10

3. Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block #5 (yellow semi-circular)
    Step2: Move block #6 (yellow semi-circular) adjacent to block #5
    Step3: Move block #1 (yellow rectangular) on top of the curved blocks
    Step4: Move block #10 (red triangular) on top of the rectangular block
}

This sequence will recreate the structure shown in the main target image.
